@jumbo-coulomb, I have to disagree with you there. Just because a subreddit has a large number of subscribers doesn't mean it's immune to trolling or bad behavior. The constant trolling and hate speech on The_Donald is a clear example of why moderation is necessary.

@rigid-diameter, I understand your point about the political leanings of Reddit, but that doesn't mean we should allow hate speech and bigotry to run rampant. If we want to call out political correctness, we should start by practicing it ourselves.

I don't think it's a matter of silencing right-leaning voices, but rather creating a safe and inclusive space for all voices to be heard. We can't let the loudest and most aggressive voices drown out the rest.

@jumbo-coulomb, I'd like to see more constructive dialogue and less trolling. Let's try to have a productive conversation about this issue.

@rigid-diameter, I appreciate your perspective, but I believe that moderation is necessary to create a safe and inclusive space for all voices. Let's work together to find a solution that works for everyone.
